# Environment variables passed into the container via `docker --env-file`.
#
# One KEY=VALUE per line. No quotes, no shell expansion — values are forwarded
# verbatim into the container environment. Blank lines and lines starting with
# `#` are ignored, so this file may safely stay empty. A per-project override at
# <config-dir>/projects/<key>/.env takes precedence over this file when present.
#
# Do NOT put MCP_GH_BEARER here. It is forwarded separately from your host shell
# (see docs/mcp-servers.md) so the host-side read-only token guard can validate
# it before the container starts, and so the token is never written to disk.
#
# Example:
#   MY_API_BASE=https://api.internal.example.com
#   FEATURE_FLAG_X=1
